The new crown pneumonia outbreak remains grim, with everyone on tenterhooks and in a somber mood.

Japan's diamond princess roams the sea, barring tourists from disembarking and reportedly infecting 14 Chinese tourists.

The hero of today's story is also related to the sea, he is a crew with HIV, the epidemic spread when he was sailing and the drug is about to stop. Let's call him Kwok Ho.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We can feel how desperate Guohao's situation at that time, like all in the epidemic due to various force majeure, ai you, after all, medicine is life. Guohao's wife, who contacted Pu Shu in Shaanxi, was distraught and said she did not want to see her husband run the risk of drug resistance due to drug withdrawal. Envy Guohao can have such a love his wife, fortunately or unfortunately, determined to be life.

When asked for help, Birchwood staff comforted his wife and promised to help them try to solve their drug withdrawal problems, while beginning to use Birchwood's huge tag to search for a patient who could help. Since its establishment, Baihualin has marked the coordinates of more than 14,000 AI friends all over the world, and the love platform of Internet interconnection and Mutual Assistance has played an important role in the epidemic.

Knowing that Guohao would stop at a port in Singapore for a short time in a few days'time, we immediately made contact with the local elite members of birchwood forest in Singapore to gradually coordinate the drug purchase and distribution issues. However, many obstacles followed.

First of all, Singapore is very strict on the drug control for AIDS patients, want to get the drug must be personally to a doctor to prescribe, but can only obtain half a month of drugs.

So we and our volunteers began to look for local sources of generic drugs. Since none of our volunteers had used a generic drug, the search turned out to be quite an effort, but we were able to find a generic drug that could replace the original Guohao drug combination in terms of efficacy and safety.

How to deliver the drug to Guohao's hand became the next problem. The outbreak is so severe that the Chinese crew can not go ashore, and our volunteers can not enter the port to make the handover with H. Finally, we tried to get in touch with the local intermediary company that often provides the crew with transshipment of living materials, hoping to deliver medicine for Guohao through them.

Despite the cooperation with the agency, due to the privacy of Guohao, we can not send the drug to the agency by express delivery, because the name of the drug must be registered in the real name and the prescription must be provided, eventually, the volunteers handed the packets to the agents themselves. In fact, after every call for help, the most difficult is our volunteers around. They are one of ai you's, but out of simple solidarity, they always try their best to solve every problem, it is the selfless dedication of everyone in this group that makes Pu Shu's platform of love more solid, and makes the strength and warmth of the group felt by more people who have been helpless.

Such a cross-regional help, each link is full of unknown difficulties. For example, the cost of the settlement issue, seemingly transfer such a simple procedure in foreign countries did not popularize Wechat, alipay under the circumstances is extremely difficult. At that time the situation must be carried out by the intermediary in which the transfer transition, a small transaction is also to turn 18 corners. Guohao's wife was always thinking of various ways, although people in Shaanxi but coordination three places, she finally used the bank overseas remittance method to send volunteers three months of drug costs.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Such a relay to the end of the three months of Guohao medicine, domestic and foreign communication and mutual help is undoubtedly a timely rain, the solution to the great trouble Guohao. Guohao's wife said, is the White Birch forest saved his husband's life, they are extremely grateful, without words. Betula Platyphylla says she has been volunteering for years, and there have been setbacks, and there have been times when she almost didn't make it, but when she hears the patient's heartfelt thanks and sees the smile on their face, i have the motivation to do a good job of volunteer work, I think before all the pay is worth it, it is a kind of warmth and pride from the bottom of my heart.

We wanted to sort through some of the stories from the recent outbreak, and more to express the feeling that we needed to be together. Some people say that everyone is an island, AIDS patients are even more so, but when faced with a crisis such as the epidemic, if each of us can not connect, help each other, then how much hope and hope? Birchwood has been trying to build a network, a network of all AIDS patients can watch each other, AIDS after you, still love you.
